                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760221-36-off194 t17760221-36-cd195"></join>.</p>
               <p>JOHN BROWN sworn.</p>
               <p>I live in <placeName id="t17760221-36-crimeloc196">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17760221-36-crimeloc196" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17760221-36-crimeloc196" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760221-36-off194 t17760221-36-crimeloc196"></join>: I lost a scarlet cloth cloak out of my shop; my brother told me the prisoner took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760221-36-person375">
                  WILLIAM
                   BROWN
               <interp inst="t17760221-36-person375" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760221-36-person375" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760221-36-person375" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. I live with my brother, who is a <rs id="t17760221-36-viclabel197" type="occupation">mercer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760221-36-victim374 t17760221-36-viclabel197"></join> in Oxford-street; I saw the prisoner take the cloak off the bar of the door, about two o'clock. I was in an adjoining room to the shop.</p>
               <p>What do you call the bar of the door? - The bar that secures it in the night; I saw the prisoner come in and take the cloak, and give it to a soldier; I pursued them, and took the prisoner; the soldier threw the cloak into a draper's shop.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I never was in the shop at all.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17760221-36-verdict198" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17760221-36-verdict198" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the Second Middlesex Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
